snippet.textDisplay:
This song is deeply melancholic and beautifully woven with Assamese folk elements. As lyricist Himangshu explained in an interview, the first two verses are inspired by a Moran lullaby for a newborn elephant, while the rest of the song blends Deuri and other Assamese folk traditions.

The lyrics carry a profound sense of longing and separation. The first part reflects the sorrow of a baby elephant being taken from its mother for training. The latter part shifts to the perspective of the mahout, who leaves behind his home, family, love, and youth to live in the jungle for days, dedicating his life to training elephants. The way these themes of sacrifice and departure intertwine is truly mesmerizing!
